headline_main: Winners and Losers of the Democratic Debate
byline_original: By The New York Times Opinion

abstract: In New Hampshire, the Democratic field defines itself, unflatteringly, as “cool newcomer” vs. “establishment experience.”
snippet: In New Hampshire, the Democratic field defines itself, unflatteringly, as “cool newcomer” vs. “establishment experience.”
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — For months, he played the big-talking front-runner, swaggering if rarely steady, hoping voters would not linger long on the tautology of his premise: Joe Biden was the candidate who should win, he told fellow Democrats, because he was the candidate who could win.

abstract: In Iowa and New Hampshire, it’s Mr. Buttigieg — not Bernie Sanders — who has complicated Ms. Warren’s path, winning over college-educated white voters using a similar message of Democratic unity.
snippet: In Iowa and New Hampshire, it’s Mr. Buttigieg — not Bernie Sanders — who has complicated Ms. Warren’s path, winning over college-educated white voters using a similar message of Democratic unity.
lead_paragraph: MERRIMACK N.H. — In the back row of an event geared toward veterans for Pete Buttigieg, the former mayor of South Bend, Ind., on Thursday, a discussion broke about one of his Democratic rivals — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts.

headline_main: The Harrowing Chaos of the Democratic Primary
headline_print_headline: The Harrowing Chaos of the Democratic Primary

abstract: A New York Times survey of the Democratic presidential hopefuls found differences on Israel, North Korea, cyberweapons and the use of military force.
snippet: A New York Times survey of the Democratic presidential hopefuls found differences on Israel, North Korea, cyberweapons and the use of military force.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Andrew Yang say that if elected, they would continue President Trump’s personal diplomacy with Kim Jong-un of North Korea. But Joseph R. Biden Jr., Michael R. Bloomberg and Amy Klobuchar would not: That approach has just propped up a dictator while his nuclear arsenal expands, Mr. Biden argues.
